{"page_content": "Even if the system is shown to do individual subtasks reliably, this still raises the problem of how\nto evaluate whether the agent will reliably chain these actions together. Finally, agentic systems\nmay be expected to succeed under a wide range of conditions, but the real world contains a long tail\nof tasks which are di\ufb03cult to de\ufb01ne and events which are hard to anticipate in advance (including\nthose that emerge from human-agent or agent-agent interactions). Similar di\ufb03culties with evaluating\nreliability under unanticipated conditions have signi\ufb01cantly slowed the deployment of self-driving\n8", "metadata": {"producer": "LuaTeX-1.16.0", "creator": "LaTeX with hyperref", "creationdate": "2023-12-18T15:56:58+00:00", "source": "D:\\Users\\wpoga\\Documents\\Ebooks\\Artificial Intelligence\\practices-for-governing-agentic-ai-systems.pdf", "file_path": "D:\\Users\\wpoga\\Documents\\Ebooks\\Artificial Intelligence\\practices-for-governing-agentic-ai-systems.pdf", "total_pages": 23, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2023-12-18T15:56:58+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20231218155658Z", "creationDate": "D:20231218155658Z", "page": 7}, "type": "Document"}
